        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The scheme &quot;Skill Development in ESDM for Digital India&quot; has been implemented by the Ministry of Electronics and Information Technology, Government of India. It aims to provide skill development training to 3,28,000 candidates in the Electronics System Design and Manufacturing (ESDM) sector. Through this scheme, financial assistance for training (75% for General category and 100% for Scheduled Caste, Scheduled Tribe, and Economically Weaker Section candidates) and 100% reimbursement of certification fees are provided to students, unemployed youth, and school dropouts. The scheme is implemented by Key Implementing Agencies, including National Institute of Electronics and Information Technology, Electronics Sector Skills Council of India, and Telecom Sector Skill Council.\n> **Objectives:**\n\n\n- To provide financial assistance for skill development in the ESDM sector across all States and Union Territories.\n- To facilitate skill development of students and unemployed youth through National Skills Qualifications Framework-compliant courses from Level 1 to Level 5.\n- To increase the availability of skilled manpower for the electronics industry to support the Digital India initiative.\n\n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "**1. Financial Assistance for Course Fee:**\n\n- General Category:\n\n\n\n  - 75% of course fee reimbursed by MeitY after certification and placement.\n  - Remaining 25% payable by the candidate (may be shared/borne by the Training Partner).\n\n- Reserved Category (SC/ST/EWS):\n\n  - 100% of the course fee reimbursed by MeitY.\n\n\n**2. Course Fee Structure (Upper Ceiling):**\nLevelManufacturing Courses (₹)Service Courses (₹)Max HoursL1-L29,780/-8,380/-200hrsL314,670/-12,570/-300hrsL417,115/-14,665/-350hrsL519,560/-16,760/-400hrs\n- Base Cost:\n\n  - ₹41.90/hour (Service Sector)\n  - ₹48.90/hour (Manufacturing Sector)\n\n\n**3. Registration-cum-Certification Fee (RCCF)**\n\n- Range: ₹762/- to ₹1,905/- (depending on level)\n- Paid upfront by the candidate\n- Refund (one time only) after successful certification:\n\n\n\n  - General: 75% reimbursed\n  - Reserved: 100% reimbursed\n\n\n**4. Reimbursement Structure**\n\n- 80% on successful certification\n- 20% on successful placement\n\n**5. Placement-Linked Benefit**\n\n- Minimum 70% placement required for full reimbursement\n- Placement tracking is mandatory for 3 months\n\n<br>\n\n",
        "exclusions_md": "<br>\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme aims to skill 3,28,000 candidates in the ESDM sector. Through this scheme, training and certification benefits are provided to students and unemployed youth.",
        "detailedDescription": [
